-- Mehta to Get French Loan for Uganda Sugar Plant, New Vision Says
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2012-06-27T09:36:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/mehta-to-get-french-loan-for-uganda-sugar-plant-new-vision-says.html
India’s Mehta Group will get a $23
million loan from Proparco, the private investment unit of the
French Development Agency, to expand its Ugandan sugar plant,
 New Vision  reported, citing Mahendra Mehta, the group’s chairman.  The 10-year loan will enable Sugar Corporation of Uganda
Ltd. to double production to 100,000 tons by 2015, the Kampala-
based newspaper reported. It didn’t provide details of the loan
agreement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in  Kampala  at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
